Data

What data set are you using?

We are using a data set from Kaggle which covers the history of English football âsoccerâ in the Premiere League, from 1993 to current date. Data: Date (Numeric Discrete, Categorical Ordinal), Season (Numeric Discrete, Categorical Ordinal), HomeTeam (Categorical), AwayTeam (Categorical), FTH Goals (Numeric Discrete), FTA Goals (Numeric Discrete), FT Result (Categorical), HTH Goals (Numeric Discrete), HTA Goals (Numeric Discrete), HT Result (Categorical), Referee (Categorical), H Shots (Numeric Discrete), A Shots (Numeric Discrete), H Sot (Numeric Discrete), A Sot (Numeric Discrete), H Fouls (Numeric Discrete), A Fouls (Numeric Discrete), H Corners (Numeric Discrete) A Corners (Numeric Discrete), H Yellow (Numeric Discrete), A Yellow (Numeric Discrete), H Red (Numeric Discrete), A Red (Numeric Discrete), Display_Order (Numeric Discrete, Categorical Ordinal), League (Categorical)

There is 25 variables in total. FTH and FTH represent Full Time Home and Full Time Away to depict the teams. H represents the Home team, A represents the Away team. SOT means Shots on Target. Yellow and Red represent card colors for how severe of a foul is inflicted. HT represents half-time and FT represents full-time. All of the data is soccer/football terms collected from match history.

Anova

fouls_data <- England |>
  select(`H Fouls`, `A Fouls`) |>
  pivot_longer(cols = everything(), names_to = "team_type", values_to = "fouls") |>
  mutate(team_type = ifelse(team_type == "H Fouls", "Home", "Away"))

anova_model <- aov(fouls ~ team_type, data = fouls_data)
summary(anova_model)
